section.section:
A commissioner or employee of the Board:
May not have any interest, direct or indirect, either proprietary or by means of any loan, mortgage or lien, or in any other manner, in or on any premises where alcoholic beverages are manufactured, distributed, or sold;
May not have any interest, direct or indirect, in any business wholly or partially devoted to the manufacture, distribution, or sale of alcoholic beverages;
May not own any stock in any corporation which has any interest, proprietary or otherwise, direct or indirect, in any premises where alcoholic beverages are manufactured, distributed, or sold or in any business wholly or partially devoted to the manufacture, distribution, or sale of alcoholic beverages; or
May not receive any salary or other compensation or any other thing of value from a business engaged in the manufacture, distribution, or sale of alcoholic beverages.

The chairman of the Board:
Is its administrative officer and is charged with the duty of enforcing the provisions of this article;
Shall personally supervise the activities and investigations of the several inspectors and other employees of the Board;
Shall examine the location and general character of the licensees in the City; and
Shall make recommendations to the Board concerning zoning of licensees, methods of enforcement, and promulgation of regulations to carry out the purposes of this article.

As of October 1, 1997:
Inspectors are part of the classified civil service of the City;
The Board may appoint and remove inspectors only in accordance with the provisions of law that govern classified civil service employees of the City;
An employee of the Board may not solicit or receive, directly or indirectly or on behalf of another person, a commission, political contribution, remuneration, or gift from:
An employee or other person specified in sub-subparagraph 3 of this subparagraph who violates the provisions of that sub-subparagraph is subject to the penalties specified in § 16-503 of this article.

The following is the schedule of City Union of Baltimore (CUB) salary grade levels for employees of the Board:
Office Assistant - Grade 082;
Inspector I - Grade 082;
Inspection Division Office Assistant - Grade 082;
Inspector II - Grade 085;
Accounting Assistant II - Grade 085;
Secretary III - Grade 086;
311 Call Center Supervisor - Grade 093;
Inspector III - Grade 088;
Assistant Executive Secretary - Grade 099;
Assistant Chief Inspector - Grade 097; and
Chief Inspector - Grade 099.

The inspector shall:
Have all the powers of a peace officer of this State in respect to the enforcement of the alcoholic beverages laws of the county;
Make an oath, as provided in the Constitution of Maryland, to faithfully perform the duties entrusted to him;
Visit and inspect at unannounced times every licensed premises in the county at least every 90 days; and
Make monthly reports in writing to the Board covering his activities, setting forth any complaints, and listing any violations that may have been observed or reported to the inspector.

An alcoholic beverages inspector has the following powers and duties:
To investigate all applicants for an alcoholic beverages license or transfer of license;
To enforce all alcoholic beverages laws of Kent County with the same powers as a law enforcement officer of the State;
To inspect, at unannounced times, every licensed premises at least once every 90 days;
To investigate all violations of the alcoholic beverages laws;
To report all violations of the alcoholic beverages laws to the Board; and
To give monthly written reports to the Board covering all:
Inspection activities;
Complaints; and
Violations, either observed or reported.

A member of the Board may not:
Have any interest, direct or indirect, either proprietary or by means of any loan, mortgage or lien, or in any other manner, in or on any premises where alcoholic beverages are manufactured or sold;
Have any interest, direct or indirect, in any business wholly or partially devoted to the manufacture or sale of alcoholic beverages;
Own any stock in any corporation which has any interest, proprietary or otherwise, direct or indirect, in any premises where alcoholic beverages are manufactured or sold or in any business wholly or partially devoted to the manufacture or sale of alcoholic beverages; or
Hold any other public office, federal, State or local.

The inspectors shall:
Each have all the powers of a peace officer or a constable or sheriff of this State;
Make oath to faithfully perform the duties entrusted to them, as provided in Article I, § 9 of the Maryland Constitution;
Be known as "alcoholic beverages inspectors for Prince George's County";
Have the duty of visiting and inspecting every licensed premises periodically; and
Carry on the other duties the Board prescribes.
